text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia anaticeps is a shrub or tree of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Kimberley and Pilbara regions of Western Australia.The glabrous shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 1 to 4 metres (3 to 13 ft). It blooms from April to June and produces yellow flowers.
